<exercise checkit-seed="0001" checkit-slug="SQ1" checkit-title="Sequence formulas">
    <statement>
        <ol>
            <li>
                Find the first 5 terms of the following sequence:
                <ul>
                    <li><m>a_n=-\left(\frac{1}{4}\right)^{n}.</m></li>
                    ,
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                Find a closed form for the following sequence:
                <ul>
                    <li><m>4, 5, 8, 13, 20,\ldots</m></li>
                    ,
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                Find a recursive form for the following sequence:
                <ul>
                    <li><m>3, -2, -7, -12, -17,\ldots</m></li>
                    ,
                </ul>
            </li>
            
            
        </ol>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <ul>
                    <li><m>-\frac{1}{4}, -\frac{1}{16}, -\frac{1}{64}, -\frac{1}{256}, -\frac{1}{1024}</m> if you start with <m> n=1</m>, or <m>-1, -\frac{1}{4}, -\frac{1}{16}, -\frac{1}{64}, -\frac{1}{256}</m> if you start with <m> n=0</m>.</li>
                    ,
                </ul>
            </li>
            
            <li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Answers can vary depending on your choice of starting index.  For example, <m>n^{2} + 4</m> if <m> n=0,1,...</m>.</li>
                    ,
                </ul>
            </li>
            
            <li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Answers can vary depending on your choice of starting index.  For example, if <m>a_0=3</m> then <m>a_n=1a_{n-1}+-5</m>.</li>
                    ,
                </ul>
            </li>
            
           
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
